MerFran

Ah, gees. I wouldn't really have expected that, but - yes, there are areas of the US where seasons do not exist (they're all "4-season-free zones," so far as I know ),

But then, my climate zone (on the higher side of the same climate zone as most of the US Gulf/East Coast) is extremely seasonal. Everyone who lives here - whatever they were born here or merely chose to move here - is acutely aware of the seasons. We have, more than any other place I've ever lived, a strong "homebody" or "cave" feeling during winter. Some embrace that, some *have* to adapt. (My husband just naturally embraces winter)

I am really disappointed by all the replies I got so far :(
